1 Championship qualification]] \n|-\n!scope=row|3\n| 6 June 2012 || [[Est\u00e1dio Municipal da Marinha Grande]], [[Marinha Grande]], [[Portugal]] || align=center | 7 || {{fbu|21|Portugal}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20132 || align=center | 1\u20133 || 2013 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification \n|}\n\n:{{updated|25 March 2019}}. ''Albania score listed first, score column indicates score after each Balaj's goal.''<ref name=\"EU-Football.info\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col data-sort-type=date|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n|-\n!scope=row|1\n| 7 September 2014 || [[Est\u00e1dio Municipal de Aveiro]], [[Aveiro, Portugal|Aveiro]], Portugal || align=center | 5 || {{fb|Portugal}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group I|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]  \n|-\n!scope=row|2\n| 5 September 2016 || [[Loro Bori\u00e7i Stadium]], [[Shkod\u00ebr]], Albania || align=center | 17 || {{fb|Macedonia}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20131 || align=center | 2\u20131 ||rowspan=2| [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group G|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] \n|-\n!scope=row|3\n| 6 October 2016 || [[Rheinpark Stadion]], [[Vaduz]], Liechtenstein || align=center | 18 || {{fb|Liechtenstein}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20130 || align=center | 2\u20130 \n|-\n!scope=row|4\n| 28 March 2017 || rowspan=2|[[Elbasan Arena]], [[Elbasan]], Albania || align=center | 21 || {{fb|Bosnia}} || align=center |'''1'''\u20132 || align=center |1\u20132 ||rowspan=2| [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n!scope=row|5\n| 20 November 2018 || align=center | 30 || {{fb|Wales}} || align=center |'''1'''\u20130 || align=center |1\u20130\n|-\n!scope=row|6\n| 25 March 2019 || [[Estadi Nacional]], [[Andorra la Vella]], Andorra || align=center | 31 || {{fb|Andorra}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group H|UEFA Euro 2020 qualification]]  \n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr\n* [[Albanian Cup]]: [[2007\u201308 Albanian Cup|2007\u201308]]; Runner-up: [[2009\u201310 Albanian Cup|2009\u201310]]\n* [[Albanian Superliga]] Runner-up: [[2008\u201309 Albanian Superliga|2008\u201309]]\n\n;Tirana<ref name=\"Soccerway profile\"/>\n* [[Albanian Cup]]: [[2010\u201311 Albanian Cup|2010\u201311]], [[2011\u201312 Albanian Cup|2011\u201312]]\n* [[Albanian Supercup]]: [[2011 Albanian Supercup|2011]]\n\n;Sparta Prague<ref name=\"Soccerway profile\"/>\n* [[Czech First League]] Runner-up: [[2012\u201313 Czech First League|2012\u201313]]\n\n;Rijeka<ref name=\"Soccerway profile\"/>\n* [[Croatian First Football League]] Runner-up: [[2014\u201315 Croatian First Football League|2014\u201315]], [[2015\u201316 Croatian First Football League|2015\u201316]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Albanian Superliga Talent of the Season]]: [[2011\u201312 Albanian Superliga|2011\u201312]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gazeta-shqip.com/lajme/2012/05/30/bekim-bales-i-jepet-cmimi-talenti-i-sezonit-2011-2012/|title=Bekim Bal\u00ebs i jepet \u00e7mimi \u201cTalenti i sezonit 2011-2012\u201d|date=30 May 2012|publisher=Gazeta Shqip|language=Albanian|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bekim Balaj}} \n* {{90minut|23600}}\n* {{Soccerway|bekim-balaj/83012}}\n* {{hrnogomet|3003}}\n* {{UEFA player|250002979}}\n* {{NFT player|id=49384}}\n* [http://euro.fshf.org/bekim-balaj/ Bekim Balaj \u2013 Euro 2016 profile] at [[FSHF]].org\n\n{{SK Sturm Graz squad}}\n{{Albania squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balaj, Bekim}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Shkod\u00ebr]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr players]]\n[[Category:KF Tirana players]]\n[[Category:Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:AC Sparta Prague players]]\n[[Category:Jagiellonia Bia\u0142ystok players]]\n[[Category:SK Slavia Prague players]]\n[[Category:HNK Rijeka players]]\n[[Category:FC Akhmat Grozny players]]\n[[Category:SK Sturm Graz players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Czech First League players]]\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Croatian First Football League players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Poland]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Russia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Austria]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Poland]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Russia]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Austria]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Bekim Balaj\n| image       = Bekim Balaj 2016.jpg\n| caption     = Balaj with FC Terek in 2016\n| fullname    = Bekim Abdyl Balaj\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1991|1|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Shkod\u00ebr]], [[Albania]]\n| height      = 1.88 m \n| position    = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] \n| currentclub = [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]]\n| clubnumber  = 9\n| youthyears1 = 2002\u20132009 | youthclubs1 = [[KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] \n| years1 = 2009\u20132010   | clubs1 = [[KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] | caps1 = 38 | goals1 = 17 \n| years2 = 2010\u20132011   | clubs2 = [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]]   | caps2 = 1  | goals2 = 0 \n| years3 = 2011\u20132012   | clubs3 = [[KF Tirana|Tirana]]                     | caps3 = 37 | goals3 = 16 \n| years4 = 2012\u20132014   | clubs4 = [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]       | caps4 = 12 | goals4 = 3 \n| years5 = 2013\u20132014   | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Jagiellonia Bia\u0142ystok]] (loan)       | caps5 = 31 | goals5 = 7 \n| years6 = 2014\u20132015   | clubs6 = [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]]       | caps6 = 13 | goals6 = 3 \n| years7 = 2015\u20132016   | clubs7 = [[HNK Rijeka|Rijeka]]                    | caps7 = 46 | goals7 = 18 \n| years8 = 2016\u20132019   | clubs8 = [[FC Akhmat Grozny|Akhmat Grozny]]       | caps8 = 61 | goals8 = 12 \n| years9 = 2019\u2013       | clubs9 = [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]]             | caps9 = 17 | goals9 = 5\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\u20132010 | nationalteam1 = [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania U19]]  | nationalcaps1 =  6 | nationalgoals1 = 3\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\u20132012 | nationalteam2 = [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U21]]  | nationalcaps2 =  8 | nationalgoals2 = 3\n| nationalyears3 = 2012\u2013     | nationalteam3 = [[Albania national football team|Albania]]               | nationalcaps3 = 37 | nationalgoals3 = 7\n|medaltemplates = \n| club-update          = 2 November 2019\n| nationalteam-update  = 11 October 2019\n}}\n\n'''Bekim Abdyl Balaj''' (born 11 January 1991) is an Albanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for Austrian club [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] and the [[Albania national football team|Albania national team]].\n\nBalaj started his football career with his hometown club [[Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] and made his professional debut at the age of 17 before going on to score 17 goals in 38 games for the club before moving to Turkey to join [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]].<ref name=\"World Bulletin\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldbulletin.net/general/turkish-team-signs-albanian-striker-h60103.html|title=Turkish team signs Albanian striker|publisher=World Bulletin|date=17 June 2010|accessdate=20 October 2019}}</ref> After little success in Turkey he returned to Albania and played for [[KF Tirana]]<ref name=\"Tirana\"/> where he scored 15 league goals in 37 games before joining [[Sparta Prague]] in the Czech Republic in January 2013.\n\nDuring his time at Sparta Prague he was loaned out to Polish side [[Jagiellonia Bia\u0142ystok]] for the entire 2013\u201314 campaign where he scored 9 goals in 36 games in all competition before return to his parent club for the first half of the following season. He joined Croatian club [[HNK Rijeka]] in January 2015 for a fee of \u20ac600,000.<ref name=\"Rijeka\"/>\n\nBalaj begun his international career with [[Albania national under-19 football team|under-19 squad]] in 2008, and two years later also represented the [[Albania national under-19 football team|under-21 squad]]. He made his international senior debut in 2012 and played an important role in Albania's successful [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying]] campaign, notably scoring the winner with a volley in the opening day against Portugal. He was selected in the 23-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]],<ref name=\"Euro 2016 squad\"/> making his debut against [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in the final group match.<ref name=\"Win against Romania\"/>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr===\nBalaj joined his hometown club [[KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] as an 11-year-old in 2002, and his father had told the youth team coach Astrit Prem\u00e7i to initially test the player as a goalkeeper as he was tall for his age. However, after only a few training sessions with Balaj, the coach Prem\u00e7i realised the player was an able outfield player as he was good with his feet, so he then played him as a centre forward.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportishqiptar.com.al/bala-po-perjetoj-nje-enderr-ne-turqi/|title=Bekim Bala: Po p\u00ebrjetoj nj\u00eblloj \u00ebndrre n\u00eb Turqi\u2026|author=Gjergj Kola|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Sporti Shqiptar]]|accessdate=20 June 2010|date=20 June 2010}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe was invited to train with the first team by the coach [[Mirel Josa]] during the latter stages of the 2007\u201308 season, and he made his first team debut on 17 May 2008 at the age of 17 years, 4 months and 6 days in an away game against [[Bes\u00eblidhja Lezh\u00eb]], coming on as a 70th-minute substitute for [[Albert Ka\u00e7i]] in the 4\u20132 loss.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.match.beselidhja-lezhe.vllaznia-shkoder.255656.en.html|title=Football - Match Kategoria superiore : Beselidhja Lezhe vs. Vllaznia Shkoder|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=21 March 2015|date=21 March 2015}}</ref> He became a first team regular the following season, and he scored his first senior goal on his first appearances of the campaign in an [[Albanian Cup]] tie against [[Sopoti Librazhd]], before going on to make 12 appearances in all competition, 7 of which were in the league and 10 of which were substitute appearances. He was part of the Vllaznia team that finished runners-up in the [[Albanian Superliga]], finishing 4 points behind the eventual winners [[KF Tirana]].\n\nWith the departures of [[Xhevahir Sukaj]] and [[James Boadu]] ahead of the 2009\u201310 season, Balaj became the club's main striker alongside [[Vioresin Sinani]]. He made his European debut on 2 July 2009 against Irish club [[Sligo Rovers F.C.|Sligo Rovers]], coming on as an 85th-minute substitute for Vioresin Sinani in the 2\u20131 away win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2009/07/02/europe/uefa-cup/sligo-rovers-fc/ks-vllaznia-shkoder/786449/|title=Sligo Rovers vs. Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr - 2 July 2009|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2010 he went on trial with [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|PSG]] alongside fellow Albanian youth international [[Odise Roshi]], but neither players' trial was successful.<ref>[http://www.arkivalajmeve.com/Roshi--Bala-nis-eksodi-i-shqiptareve-drejt-Evropes.1046849762/ Roshi - Bala, nis eksodi i shqiptareve drejt Evropes] Arkiva Shqiptare e Lajmeve</ref> In June, he went on another trial, this time in Turkey with [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]] and he was immediately offered a contract to join the club.\n\n===Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi===\nA top Turkish club had been tracking the young forward for most of the 2009\u20132010 season whilst he was at Vllaznia; the club was not identified in January 2010 as they did not make a bid,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=13389&l=a |title=Qipriot\u00eb dhe turq, p\u00ebr \"yjet\" e Superiores |author=Jorgis Memo |language=Albanian |publisher=Albania-Sport |accessdate=18 June 2010 |date=17 December 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929165838/http://www.albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=13389&l=a |archive-date=29 September 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> however following the huge interest shown by [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.]] in May and June, it became clear who the unnamed Turkish club was. Balaj signed a four-year contract with Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi on 17 June 2010.<ref name=\"World Bulletin\"/> The transfer fee was reported to be around \u20ac200,000 to \u20ac300,000, which was all given to his previous club Vllaznia in Albania.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=15190 |title=Bekim Balaj transferohet te Gen\u00e7lerbirligi |language=Albanian |publisher=Albania-Sport |accessdate=18 June 2010 |date=16 June 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721013029/http://www.albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=15190 |archive-date=21 July 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Balaj's manager Dritan Gjyrezi had only been a licensed FIFA agent for a year before managing this deal; this was his first deal in his career as an agent and he hoped to be able to send more Albanian players to Turkey.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sportishqiptar.com.al/gjyrezi-bala-ne-turqi-zgjedhja-me-e-mire/ |title=Gjyrezi: Bala n\u00eb Turqi, zgjedhja m\u00eb e mir\u00eb |author=Gjergj Kola |language=Albanian |publisher=[[Sporti Shqiptar]] |accessdate=18 June 2010 |date=17 June 2010 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Balaj signed the contract earning him [[Euro|\u20ac]]150,000 for the first year, making the deal to be worth around [[Euro|\u20ac]]600,000 for the full four years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldbulletin.net/news_detail.php?id=60103 |title=Turkish team signs Albanian striker |author= |language=Albanian |publisher=World Bulletin |accessdate=19 June 2010 |date=17 June 2010 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n===KF Tirana===\nIn January Balaj received offers from both [[KF Tirana]] and his former club Vllaznia for a return to Albania.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gazetashqiptareonline.com/bekim-bala-me-nje-kembe-te-tirana.html|title=Bekim Balaj, me nj\u00eb k\u00ebmb\u00eb te Tirana|author=|publisher=Gazeta Shqiptare Online|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=19 January 2011}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> But after meeting with [[Refik Halili]] he signed a two-year contract for KF Tirana on 20 January 2011, earning \u20ac70,000 a season, which was a higher offer than Vllaznia's \u20ac50,000.<ref name=\"Tirana\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arkivalajmeve.com/Bala-te-Tirana-per-70-mije-.1046983898/|title=Bala te Tirana per 70 mije|trans-title=Balaj to Tirana for 70 thousand|publisher=Arkiva Shqiptare e Lajmeve|work=Panorama Sport|language=sq|date=20 January 2011|accessdate=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yllpress.com/24234/tirana-firmos-me-sulmuesin-bekim-bala-vllaznia-huazon-abrahamin.html|title=Tirana firmos me sulmuesin Bekim Balaj|author=Gjergji Mima|publisher=Yll Press|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=21 January 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/superliga/3834.html|title=Perfundimisht:Bekim Balaj te Tirana|author=Besi Donati|publisher=Albania Soccer|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=20 January 2011}}</ref>\n\nHe made his debut for his new club on 3 February in a home match against [[Sk\u00ebnderbeu Kor\u00e7\u00eb]] which ended in 0\u20130 draw, with Balaj coming on at the start of the second half for [[Gilman Lika]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.match.kf-tirana.skenderbeu-korce.666218.en.html|title=KF Tirana 0\u20130 Sk\u00ebnderbeu|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=3 February 2011}}</ref> His first Tirana goal came in the [[Albanian Cup]] semi final second leg against [[Besa Kavaj\u00eb]] on 6 April, scoring the equalising goal to secure his side's place in the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.coupe.besa-kavaje.kf-tirana.123935.en.html|title=Besa 1\u20131 KF Tirana|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=6 April 2011}}</ref> He then went on to score his first league goal just nine days later in a 6\u20131 thrashing of [[KF Elbasani]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.match.kf-tirana.elbasani.680374.en.html|title=KF Tirana 6\u20131 KF Elbasani|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=15 April 2011}}</ref> Despite good performances since his January move, new coach [[Mi\u0161o Krsti\u010devi\u0107]] did not pick him to start in the final of the Albanian Cup. Balaj came on for Gilman Lika in the 54th minute and helped his side win the trophy despite ending the game with ten men and Balaj himself missing a penalty in the shootout which ended 4\u20133 after heroics from the keeper [[Ilion Lika]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.coupe.kf-tirana.dinamo-tirana.123936.en.html|title=KF Tirana 1\u20131 Dinamo Tirana|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=22 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=alb/news/newsid=1633348.html|title=Tirana shade Dinamo in Albanian Cup final|author=Fatjon Pandovski|publisher=[[UEFA]].com|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=22 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://lajme.shqiperia.com/lajme/artikull/iden/1047039514/titulli/Kupa-e-Shqiperise-Ilion-Lika-i-jep-titullin-e-14-te-kampion-Tiranes|title=Ilion Lika i jep titullin e 14-te kampion Tiranes|author=Altin Vorpsi|publisher=Info Arkiv|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=23 May 2011}}</ref>\n\nHe scored the winning goal in the [[Albanian Supercup 2011|2011 Albanian Supercup]] against the league winners Sk\u00ebnderbeu, in a match delayed and disrupted by crowd trouble.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/08/18/albania/super-cup/ks-skenderbeu-korce/kf-tirana/1126866/|title=Sk\u00ebnderbeu 0\u20131 KF Tirana|author=|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=18 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.coupe.skenderbeu-korce.kf-tirana.127700.en.html|title=KF Tirana 0\u20130 Sk\u00ebnderbeu|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=28 August 2011|date=18 August 2011}}</ref> \nHis first league goal of the season came on 17 September in the second week of the campaign, away at [[Kastrioti Kruj\u00eb]]. Starting the game as a lone striker, he equalised for KF Tirana in the 48th minute and helped his side win the game 3\u20132, earning their first three points of the campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.match.kastrioti-kruje.kf-tirana.727943.en.html|title=Kastrioti 2\u20133 KF Tirana|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=5 November 2011|date=17 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/09/17/albania/super-league/ks-kastrioti-kruje/kf-tirana/1212550/|title=Kastrioti 2\u20133 KF Tirana|author=|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=5 November 2011|date=17 September 2011}}</ref> Following KF Tiran's first win in the league, it had become evident that Balaj and [[Gilman Lika]] had formed an effective partnership from midfield to attack, both of whom are from [[Shkod\u00ebr]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportekspres.com/contenti.aspx?id=521&idd=562&iddd=568&idjadok=11579|title=Bala: Un\u00eb dhe Lika, \u00ebsht\u00eb nj\u00eb Tiran\u00eb \"shkodrane\"|author=Arbi La\u00e7i|publisher=[[Sport Ekspres]]|accessdate=5 November 2011|date=20 September 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111123113305/http://www.sportekspres.com/contenti.aspx?id=521|archivedate=23 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nHis next goal came just four days later in the first round of the [[Albanian Cup]] against [[SK Himar\u00eb]] of the [[Albanian First Division]]. He scored in the 36th minute, a penalty in the 52nd minute and finally rounded off his hattrick in the 67th minute, before [[Juli\u00e1n Rubio]] being forced to replace the player following a strong challenge which left him with an ankle injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballdatabase.eu/football.coupe.kf-himara.kf-tirana.128577.en.html|title=KF Himara 0\u20133 KF Tirana|author=Oltian Ru\u00e7i|publisher=Football Database|accessdate=5 November 2011|date=21 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportekspres.com/contenti.aspx?id=521&idd=562&iddd=568&idjadok=11694|title=Balaj shou, tre gola p\u00eb t\u00eb hipotekuar turin tjet\u00ebr|author=Arbi La\u00e7i|publisher=[[Sport Ekspres]]|accessdate=5 November 2011|date=22 September 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111123113305/http://www.sportekspres.com/contenti.aspx?id=521|archivedate=23 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> After scoring four goals in as many days he hoped he could one day force his way into the [[Albania national football team|Albania national team]], which he said would be a dream following a good start to the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportekspres.com/contenti.aspx?id=521&idd=562&iddd=568&idjadok=11757|title=Bala: Pasi t\u00eb fitoj Tiran\u00ebn dua komb\u00ebtaren|publisher=[[Sport Ekspres]]|accessdate=5 November 2011|date=23 September 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111123113305/http://www.sportekspres.com/contenti.aspx?id=521|archivedate=23 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Sparta Prague===\nBalaj joined [[Sparta Prague]] on trial in July 2012 in order for the manager [[V\u00edt\u011bzslav Lavi\u010dka]] to get a closer look at the player before the deal to join the club was finalised. Lavi\u010dka started with Balaj in a friendly against [[Graffin Vla\u0161im]] on 17 July. Balaj started the game brightly, getting close to scoring with a header in the 5th minute, and eventually scoring in the 19th minute with a powerful shot on goal from just outside the 18-yard box to put Sparta Prague 3\u20130 up. He was substituted at half time and the game was won by Sparta Prague 5\u20130. After the friendly he returned to Albania to sort out his contract with KF Tirana, who did not want him to leave unless they received a fee of \u20ac100,000, with Sparta Prague only offering half that sum because Bala's deal with KF Tirana was due to expire in January 2013.\n\nOn 4 October 2012, Balaj scored an historical goal in his career at [[UEFA Europa League]] against [[Athletic Bilbao]], a match valid for group stage finished in the victory 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/10/04/europe/uefa-cup/ac-sparta-praha/athletic-club/1388938/|title=Sparta Praha vs. Athletic Club - 4 October 2012 |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Jagiellonia====\nOn 8 July 2013 he moved on loan for a year to Polish side [[Jagiellonia Bia\u0142ystok]] in the [[Ekstraklasa]]. He scored his 3rd goal on 9 August 2013 against [[Wis\u0142a Krak\u00f3w]] in the 90'+3 to give his team the 1\u20131 draw.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/7694-poloni-bekim-bala-shenon-gol-in-extremis-.html Poloni/ Bekim Bala shenon gol \u201cin Extremis\u201d] AlbaniaSoccer</ref> Balaj scored twice against [[Ruch Chorz\u00f3w]] on 15 September 2013 and Jagiellonia won 6\u20130 with Balaj scoring two last goals to sent in 5 number of goals scored in the season.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/7874-legjionaret-bekim-bala-dopiete-ne-poloni-.html Legjionaret/ Bekim Bala dopiete ne Poloni] AlbaniaSoccer</ref> Balaj scored his 5th goal on 4 November 2013 against [[Piast Gliwice]] to open the score in the 56th minute but it wasn't enough as Jagiellonia got overturned 2\u20131.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/11/04/poland/ekstraklasa/gks-piast-gliwice/jagiellonia-bialystok/1478186/ Piast Gliwice vs. Jagiellonia Bia\u0142ystok - 4 November 2013] Soccerway</ref><ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/8211-legjionaret-bekim-bala-shenon-ne-poloni-.html Legjionaret/ Bekim Bala shenon ne Poloni] AlbaniaSoccer</ref>\n\n====Return to Slavia Prague====\nAfter being returned to Sparta Prague from Jagiellonia where he was loaned for a year, he signed for the city's rivals [[SK Slavia Prague]] on 10 July 2014.<ref>[http://www.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=Slavia-ziskala-utocnika-Bekima-Balaje-12557 Slavia z\u00edskala \u00fato\u010dn\u00edka Bekima Balaje] SK Slavia Praha</ref> He made it his debut on 26 July 2014 in the opening [[2014\u201315 Czech First League|2014\u201315 season]]'s match against [[1. FC Slov\u00e1cko|Slov\u00e1cko]], also his debut brought his first goal as well, as he scored the victory goal 1\u20132, where the match result came from behind 1\u20130 of the first half.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/07/26/czech-republic/czech-liga/1-fc-slovacko/sk-slavia-praha/1715723/|title=Slov\u00e1cko vs. Slavia Praha - 26 July 2014 |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/balaj-hero-ne-ceki-i-jep-fitoren-slavias/ Balaj hero n\u00eb \u00c7eki, i jep fitoren Slavias] [[Panorama Sport]]</ref> On 11 August 2014 Balaj scored the opening goal in the 17th minute of the match victory 4\u20131 against [[Slovan Liberec]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/08/10/czech-republic/czech-liga/sk-slavia-praha/fc-slovan-liberec/1715749/|title=Slavia Praha vs. Slovan Liberec - 10 August 2014 |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref> On 1 November 2014 Balaj came in as a substitute in the 84th minute and scored in the 87' the goal of advantage to bring his team the 3\u20132 victory against [[1. FK P\u0159\u00edbram|P\u0159\u00edbram]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/01/czech-republic/czech-liga/sk-slavia-praha/1fk-pribram/1715883/|title=Slavia Praha vs. P\u0159\u00edbram - 1 November 2014 |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===HNK Rijeka===\nOn 7 January 2015 Balaj signed a {{frac|2|1|2}}-year contract (with a 2-year extension option) with [[HNK Rijeka]], the runners-up in the [[Croatian First Football League]].<ref name=\"Rijeka\">{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/zyrtare-bekim-balaj-kalon-te-rijeka/|title=Zyrtare, Bekim Balaj kalon te Rijeka|trans-title=Official, Bekim Balaj goes to Rijeka|publisher=Gazeta Panorama|language=sq|date=8 January 2015|accessdate=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nk-rijeka.hr/vijest/bekim-balaj-novi-napadac-rijeke/|title=Bekim Balaj novi napada\u010d Rijeke|publisher=HNK Rijeka|language=hr|date=8 January 2015|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 February 2015 Balaj made his competitive d\u00e9but in Rijeka's 4\u20131 win against [[NK Lokomotiva]] in the [[2014\u201315 Croatian Football Cup|first leg of the Croatian Cup quarter-final]], also scoring his first goal for the club.<ref>[http://asport.al/balaj-shenon-gol-ne-kupen-e-kroacise-video/ Balaj sh\u00ebnon gol n\u00eb Kup\u00ebn e Kroacis\u00eb (video)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514034806/http://asport.al/balaj-shenon-gol-ne-kupen-e-kroacise-video/ |date=14 May 2016 }} aSport.al</ref> Balaj made his league d\u00e9but also scoring a goal. He also scored in the [[Adriatic derby]] between Rijeka and [[Hajduk Split]] on 18 February 2015, which Rijeka won 3\u20130.<ref>[http://asport.al/balaj-bekon-gol-edhe-derbin-e-kroacise-video/ Balaj \"bekon\" me gol edhe derbin e Kroacis\u00eb (+Video)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513235225/http://asport.al/balaj-bekon-gol-edhe-derbin-e-kroacise-video/ |date=13 May 2016 }} aSport.al</ref> Balaj scored his second goal in the second league game in a row and third including both championships against [[RNK Split]] in the 56th minute of the match, to give his team the 1\u20131 draw.<ref>[http://sportekspres.com/balaj-shenon-per-rijeken-ndaj-rnk-split/ Balaj sh\u00ebnon p\u00ebr Rijek\u00ebn ndaj RNK Split] [[Sport Ekspres]]</ref> During the season, Balaj scored 9 goals in 15 appearances, helping Rijeka to finished as runners-up and secure a place in the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Second qualifying round|2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League - Second qualifying round]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/croatia/1-hnl/20142015/regular-season/r25603/|title=Summary - 1. HNL - Croatia - Results, fixtures, tables and news |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref> Balaj also features in three [[2014\u201315 Croatian Cup]] matches and scored one goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/croatia/hr-nogometni-cup/20142015/s9667/final-stages/|title=Summary - HR Nogometni Cup - Croatia - Results, fixtures, tables and news |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nBalaj started a new season with Rijeka retaining his starting place on 10 July 2015 in a goalless draw against [[NK Inter Zapre\u0161i\u0107|Inter Zapre\u0161i\u0107]], but got substituted off for [[Roman Bezjak]] in the 58th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/05/29/croatia/1-hnl/nk-dinamo-zagreb/hnk-rijeka/1696843/|title=Dinamo Zagreb vs. Rijeka - 29 May 2015 |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref> A few days later Balaj made his European debut for Rijeka playing the full 90-minutes in the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League]] Second qualifying round first-leg match against [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/07/16/europe/uefa-cup/hnk-rijeka/aberdeen-fc/2049604/|title=Rijeka vs. Aberdeen - 16 July 2015 |publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref> Balaj scored his first goal of the season in his second league appearance, against [[NK Slaven Belupo Koprivnica|Slaven Belupo Koprivnica]] in a 3\u20133 draw.<ref>[http://telesport.al/shenon-bekim-balaj-i-jep-rijekes-nje-pike/ Sh\u00ebnon Bekim Balaj, i jep Rijek\u00ebs nj\u00eb pik\u00eb] Telesport</ref> During the [[2015\u201316 HNK Rijeka season|2015\u201316 season]], with 9 league goals to his account, he was one of [[2015\u201316 Croatian First Football League#Top scorers|top 10 goalscorers in the league]]. Balaj also scored once in the [[2015\u201316 Croatian Football Cup|Croatian Cup]].\n\n===Akhmat Grozny===\nOn 8 June 2016, Balaj completed a move to [[Russian Football Premier League]] side [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]] for \u20ac550,000, signing a three-year contract with the option of another year.<ref name=\"Balaj Terek\">{{cite news|publisher=[[FC Terek Grozny]]|url=http://fc-terek.ru/newslist/#7215|script-title=ru:\u00ab\u0422\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043a\u00bb \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043b \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0442 \u0441 \u043d\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438.|language=Russian|date=9 June 2016|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|publisher=[[HNK Rijeka]]|url=http://www.nk-rijeka.hr/vijest/bekim-balaj-potpisao-za-terek-grozny/|title=Bekim Balaj potpisao za Terek Grozny|date=12 June 2016|accessdate=12 June 2016|language=Croatian}}</ref> He was presented on the same day, where he was handed squad number 18.<ref name=\"Balaj Terek\"/> Balaj made his debut for the club on 31 July in the opening league match against [[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov]], playing for 59 minutes in an eventual 1\u20130 home win.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/07/31/russia/premier-league/terek-groznyi/pfk-kryliya-sovetov-samara/2246245/|title=Terek Grozny vs. Krylia Sovetov 1 \u2013 0|publisher=Soccerway|date=31 July 2016|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> It took him four matches to open his scoring account as he netted the first in the 3\u20131 away win versus [[FC Ufa|Ufa]] on 20 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/video-balaj-gjen-golin-terek-grozni-fiton-ne-transferte/|title=VIDEO/ Balaj gjen golin, Terek Grozni fiton n\u00eb transfert\u00eb|publisher=Panorama Sport|language=Albanian|date=20 August 2016|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> This was followed by another one eight days later in the 2\u20131 turnaround win against [[FC Rostov|Rostov]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/08/28/russia/premier-league/terek-groznyi/fk-rostov-na-donu/2246278/|title=Terek Grozny vs. Rostov 2 \u2013 1|publisher=Soccerway|date=28 August 2016|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> However those two goals were to open the floodgates of the strikers scoring in Russia, as he managed to score two consecutive braces in the matches against [[FC Ural Yekaterinburg|Ural]] and [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]], leading the team to the win against the latter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ligaolahraga.com/pertandingan-bola/russia-premier-league-1012/ural-vs-terek-grozni-4399960/|title=Hasil Skor Russia: Premier League, Ural Vs Terek Grozni Skor 1-4|publisher=Liga Olahraga|date=30 October 2016|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/top-stories/Football-Terek-inflict-first-league-defeat-on-Zenit/articleshow/55280789.cms|title=Football: Terek inflict first league defeat on Zenit|publisher=The Times of India|date=7 November 2016|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> For his performances Balaj was named Terek Grozny Player of the Month for October.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.supersport.al/balaj-dhe-berisha-lojtaret-e-muajit-ne-rusi/|title=Balaj dhe Berisha, Lojtar\u00ebt e Muajit n\u00eb Rusi|publisher=Super Sport Albania|language=Albanian|author=Erald Kodheli|date=5 November 2016|accessdate=10 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903163034/http://www.supersport.al/balaj-dhe-berisha-lojtaret-e-muajit-ne-rusi/|archive-date=3 September 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Starting from April's month Balaj became a bench player despite being an important player for the team playing 22 first matches as a starter. On 21 May 2017 Balaj came in as a 73rd-minute substitute during the match against [[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov Samara]] and after 3 minutes he scored the 3rd team goal in a match finished in the 3\u20131 victory.<ref>[http://sportekspres.com/balaj-3-minuta-per-te-dale-nga-kriza/ Balaj, 3 minuta p\u00ebr t\u00eb dal\u00eb nga kriza] [[Sport Ekspres]]</ref>\n\nBalaj started the 2017\u201318 season by providing an assist for the 1\u20130 winning goal against [[FC Amkar Perm]] on 16 July 2017 scored by [[L\u00e9o Jab\u00e1]]. On 27 May 2019, Akhmat confirmed that Balaj left the club as a free agent upon the expiration of his contract.<ref name=\"BalajMohammadi\">{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Akhmat Grozny]]|url=http://fc-akhmat.ru/page/10643|title=\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0434 \u041c\u043e\u0445\u0430\u043c\u043c\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u0438 \u0411\u0435\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0411\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0438\u0434\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u00ab\u0410\u0445\u043c\u0430\u0442\u00bb. \u0421\u043f\u0430\u0441\u0438\u0431\u043e \u0437\u0430 \u0432\u0441\u0435, \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0437\u044c\u044f!|trans-title=Milad Mohammadi and Bekim Balaj leave Akhmat. Thank you for everything, friends!|date=27 May 2019|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\n===Sturm Graz===\nOn 26 July 2019, he signed a contract with Austrian club [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] for the term of 2 years with a 1-year extension option.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[SK Sturm Graz]]|url=https://www.sksturm.at/de/news/kampfmannschaft/2019/teamspieler-fuer-sturm-sturm/|title=TEAMSPIELER F\u00dcR STURM-STURM|trans-title=Team player for Sturm's attack|date=26 July 2019|language=German}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth teams===\n[[File:Bekim Balaj - Albania U-21 (1).jpg|thumb|right|150px|Balaj with [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U21]] in 2009]]\nBalaj was part of the [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania U-19]] squad for the qualifying stage of the [[2009 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2009 European Championship]], where he made his debut on 8 October 2008 against [[England national under-19 football team|England]] at [[Ballymena Showgrounds]], [[Northern Ireland]] by replacing [[Guido Tepshi]] at half time and where the match finished in the 3\u20130 loss for Albania.<ref>[https://archive.today/20130105012141/http://en.archive.uefa.com/competitions/under19/fixturesresults/round=15216/match=302154/report=ev.html England U-19 3\u20130 Albania U-19] en.archive.uefa.com</ref> He scored his first and also Albania's only goal of the qualifying campaign, against Northern Ireland on 13 October 2008 at [[The Oval (Belfast)|The Oval, Belfast]] in a 2\u20131 loss.<ref>[https://archive.today/20130105034049/http://en.archive.uefa.com/competitions/under19/fixturesresults/round=15216/match=302206/index.html Albania U-19 1\u20132 Northern Ireland U-19] en.archive.uefa.com</ref>\n\nBalaj was called up at [[Albania national under-20 football team|Albania national under-20 side]] by coach [[Artan Bushati]] to participate in the [[Football at the 2009 Mediterranean Games|2009 Mediterranean Games football tournament]], which began on 25 June in [[Pescara]], [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.arkivalajmeve.com/Peskara-2009-Shqiperia-zbardh-listen-e-futbollisteve.260840/|title=Peskara 2009, Shqip\u00ebria zbardh list\u00ebn e futbollist\u00ebve|trans-title=Pescara 2009, Albania unveils the list of footballers|publisher=Arkiva Shqiptare e Lajmeve|language=Albanian|date=17 June 2009|accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref> However he didn't featured in the tournament.\n\nHe was part of the [[Albania national under-21 football team|under-21]] side in their [[2011 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 10|2011]] and the [[2013 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 6|2013 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] campaigns, scoring four goals in 13 matches.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2011/teams/team=200002/squad/index.html|title=Albania - Under-21|publisher=UEFA.com|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Senior team===\nBalaj made his debut for [[Albania national football team]] on 17 February 2010 in the unofficial match against [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]], where he scored a goal.<ref>[http://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/13422/Kosovo_Albania.html Kosovo vs. Albania (2:3)] National Football Teams</ref> He received his first official call up by coach [[Gianni De Biasi]] for the friendly match against [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] on 14 November 2012.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/6851-kombetarja-fshf-publikon-listen-zyrtare-.html Kombetarja/ FSHF publikon list\u00ebn zyrtare] AlbaniaSoccer</ref>\n\nBalaj was called up for the first time in competitive matches for Albania for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification - UEFA Group E|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] two closing games against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] and [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] on 11 and 15 October 2013.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/8017-kombetarja-de-biazi-publikon-listen-e-lojtareve.html Kombetarja/ De Biazi publikon listen e lojtareve] AlbaniaSoccer</ref> He made his competitive international debut in the final match of the 2014 FIFA World Cup qualification on 15 October 2013 against Cyprus where he came in as a substitute in place of [[Hamdi Salihi]] in the 87th minute of the match which finished 0\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/10/15/europe/wc-qualifying-europe/cyprus/albania/1228291/|title=Cyprus vs. Albania 0 \u2013 0|publisher=Socceray|date=15 October 2013|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n====UEFA Euro 2016 campaign====\nHe scored his first competitive goal for [[Albania national football team|Albania]] on 7 September 2014 against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in the opening match of the [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group I|UEFA Euro 2016 qualifier]], which Albania won 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/09/07/europe/european-championship-qualification/portugal/albania/1653150/|title=Portugal vs. Albania 0 \u2013 1|publisher=Soccerway|date=7 September 2014|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/239815/|title=\"Bekim\" kuqezi n\u00eb Aveiro, Shqip\u00ebria shokon Portugalin\u00eb|publisher=Panorama Sport|language=Albanian|date=7 September 2014|accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref> [[Odise Roshi]] swung in a cross from the right which was behind Balaj, but on the turn he managed to get his foot to the ball and his right-footed volley found the bottom corner from 15 yards.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/sep/07/portugal-euro-2016-defeat-albania|title=Portugal slump to home defeat by Albania in Euro 2016 qualifier|publisher=The Guardian|date=8 September 2014|accessdate=8 September 2014}}</ref> Balaj described his goal as a \"striker\" goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013821/postmatch/quotes/index.html|title=Albania enjoy afterglow of Portugal success|publisher=UEFA.com|date=7 September 2014|accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 May 2016, Balaj was named in Albania's preliminary 27-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=2366548.html|title=De Biasi leaves out Albanian top scorer Salihi|publisher=UEFA|author=Fatjon Pandovski|date=21 May 2016|accessdate=30 May 2016}}</ref> and in Albania's final 23-man UEFA Euro 2016 squad on 31 May.<ref name=\"Euro 2016 squad\">{{cite news|url=http://euro.fshf.org/de-biasi-shpall-listen-zyrtare-te-euro-2016/|title=De Biasi shpall list\u00ebn zyrtare t\u00eb Euro 2016|trans-title=De Biasi announces the official list of Euro 2016|publisher=FSHF.org|language=sq|date=31 May 2016|accessdate=31 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nBalaj was an unused substitute in two first matches against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in a 0\u20131 loss and hosts [[France national football team|France]] where they lost 2\u20130, then played as a substitute in the next match against [[Romania national football team|Romania]] for [[Armando Sadiku]] which scored the goal for the historical 1\u20130 Albania's win.<ref name=\"Win against Romania\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/06/19/albania-vs-romania-euro-2016---live/|title=Euro 2016: Romania 0 Albania 1 - Armando Sadiku scores the only goal to seal his country's first ever win at a major competition|publisher=The Telegraph|author=Richard Amofa|date=19 June 2016|accessdate=20 October 2019}}</ref> Albania finished the group in the third position with three points and with a goal difference \u20132, and was ranked last in the third-placed teams, which eventually eliminated them.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/albania-out-euro-2016-after-portugal-draw-hungary|title=Albania out of Euro 2016 after Portugal draw with Hungary|publisher=Fourfourtwo.com|date=22 June 2016|accessdate=9 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n====2018 FIFA World Cup qualification====\nIn the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group G|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] opening match against [[Macedonia national football team|Macedonia]] on 5 September 2016, Balaj came in as a 60th substitute replacing the [[Midfielder]] [[Amir Abrashi]] to play in the attack line forming a duo partnership among [[Armando Sadiku]].<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/worldcup/season=2018/matches/round=2000717/match=2017810/postmatch/lineups/index.html FIFA World Cup 2018 - Albania-FYR Macedonia] [[UEFA]].com</ref> In the 75th minute the match was interrupted at score 1\u20131 due to the weather conditions and the remained 15 minutes were played in the next day. In the penultimate minute Balaj scored a goal to give Albania's the 2\u20131 victory.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/8858-shqiperia-ben-te-pamunduren-fiton-ne-15-minuta.html Shqiperia ben te pamunduren, fiton ne 15 minuta] AlbaniaSoccer</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBekim Balaj spent and helped to build houses for the families of fallen [[Kosovo Liberation Army|National Liberation Army]] soldiers.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|13 May 2018}}<ref name=\"Soccerway profile\">{{Soccerway|bekim-balaj/83012|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"NFT\">{{NFT player|id=49384|accessdate=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] \n|[[2007\u201308 Albanian Superliga|2007\u201308]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Albanian Superliga]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Albanian Superliga|2008\u201309]]\n|7||0||5||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||12||1\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Albanian Superliga|2009\u201310]]\n|30||9||6||3||4<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UEL\">All appearance(s) in [[UEFA Europa League]]</ref>||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||40||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!38!!9!!11!!4!!4!!0!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!53!!13\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]] \n|[[2010\u201311 S\u00fcper Lig|2010\u201311]]\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[S\u00fcper Lig]]\n|1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[KF Tirana|Tirana]] \n|[[2010\u201311 Albanian Superliga|2010\u201311]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Albanian Superliga]]\n|13||2||4||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||17||3\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Albanian Superliga|2011\u201312]]\n|24||13||14||8||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UEL\"/>||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||40||21\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Albanian Superliga|2012\u201313]]\n|colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UEL\"/>||0||1<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Appearance in [[Albanian Supercup]]</ref>||1||3||1\n|-\n!colsp