{"title_page": "Cookie Jar (EP)", "text_new": "{{Correct title|title=#Cookie Jar|reason=hash}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = <nowiki>#</nowiki>Cookie Jar\n| type       = EP\n| artist     = [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]\n| cover      = Red_Velvet_Cookie_Jar_Album_Cover.jpg\n| border     = yes\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|07|04}}\n| recorded   = 2017\u20132018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[J-pop]]|[[electropop]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7857154/red-velvet-red-flavor-song-video | title=Red Velvet Offers a Taste of Summer with 'Red Flavor' Song & Video: Watch}}</ref>|[[synth-pop]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dc.koreatimes.com/article/20160903/1009584 |accessdate=September 6, 2016 |last1=Jo|first1=In-woo |website=The Korea Times |date=September 3, 2016|title=\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, '\ub7ec\uc2dc\uc548 \ub8f0\ub81b'\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31|language=Korean}}</ref>}}\n| length     = {{Duration|m=19|s=49}}\n| language   = [[Japanese language|Japanese]]\n| label      = [[Avex Trax]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Perfect Velvet]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = [[Summer Magic (Red Velvet EP)|Summer Magic]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = <nowiki>#</nowiki>Cookie Jar\n | type        = EP\n | single1     = #Cookie Jar\n | single1date = July 4, 2018\n}}\n{{External music video|type=ep|{{YouTube|rRgTMs_bGuI|\"#Cookie Jar\"}}}}\n}}\n\n'''''#Cookie Jar''''' ''(Hashtag Cookie Jar)'' is the debut Japanese [[extended play]] (sixth overall) by South Korean girl group [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]].<ref name=\"SBS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2018/05/15/red-velvet-announce-new-mini-album-cookie-jar|title=Red Velvet announce new mini-album 'Cookie Jar'|publisher=Special Broadcasting Service Australia|date=15 May 2018|access-date=30 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Mini-LP\">{{cite web|url=https://redvelvet-jp.net/discography/detail.php?id=1015795|title= JAPAN 1st mini ALBUM\u300c#Cookie Jar\u300d|publisher=Red Velvet|access-date=30 July 2018}}</ref> It was released on July 4, 2018, by [[Avex Trax]] and features the lead single of the same name.\n\n== Background and release ==\nOn May 23, 2018, the group announced the release of their debut Japanese album titled ''#Cookie Jar'' for July 4, through their official Japanese website,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redvelvet-jp.net/news/detail.php?id=1061664|title=Red Velvet JAPAN 1st mini album\u300c# Cookie Jar\u300d\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u8a18\u5ff5\u3001\u8cfc\u5165\u8005\u9650\u5b9a\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\u5fdc\u52df\u62bd\u9078\u7279\u5178\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01\uff01|website=Red Velvet \u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|language=ja|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref> declaring it to be their first [[mini-album]] in the region.<ref name=\"SBS\"/>\n\nThe first three tracks on the mini-album are new, while tracks four to six are Japanese versions of the previous singles \"Dumb Dumb\", \"Russian Roulette\" and \"Red Flavor\", off ''[[The Red (album)|The Red]]'', ''[[Russian Roulette (Red Velvet EP)|Russian Roulette]]'' and ''[[The Red Summer (EP)|The Red Summer]]'' releases, respectively.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=Red Velvet's First Japanese Single '#Cookie Jar' Is a Full-Blown Sugar Rush: Watch |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8462110/red-velvet-cookie-video |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=Billboard |date=June 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe mini-album was released on July 4, 2018.<ref>{{Citation|title=Red Velvet\u306e\u300c#Cookie Jar - EP\u300d|date=2018-07-04|url=https://itunes.apple.com/jp/album/cookie-jar-ep/1400640685|language=ja-JP|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref> There are two editions of the album released. The first one is the First Press Limited Edition, which contains a CD, a 24-page booklet and a random photo card out of 6 types packed in a deluxe mini box packaging. The second one is the Regular Edition, a jewel case that contains a CD, a 16-page booklet and a random photo card out of 6 types.\n\n== Commercial performance ==\n''#Cookie Jar'' debuted and peaked at number 3 on [[Oricon Albums Chart|Oricon]]'s Weekly Album Chart, selling 26,124 physical copies.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2018-07-16/|title=2018\u5e7407\u670802\u65e5\uff5e2018\u5e7407\u670808\u65e5 \u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u9031\u9593 \u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0|work=ORICON NEWS|access-date=2018-07-21|language=ja-JP}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711190434/https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2018-07-16/|title=\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u9031\u9593 \u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2018\u5e7407\u670802\u65e5\uff5e2018\u5e7407\u670808\u65e5 {{!}} ORICON NEWS|date=2018-07-11|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref> It also entered and peaked at number 4 on [[Billboard Japan]]'s Hot Albums and at number 13 on US [[Billboard charts|World Albums]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot_albums&year=2018&month=07&day=16|title=Billboard Japan Hot Albums {{!}} Charts {{!}} Billboard JAPAN|work=Billboard JAPAN|access-date=2018-07-21|language=ja-JP}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/red-velvet/chart-history/world-albums|title=Red Velvet Chart History|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref> The mini-album has sold over 28,130 copies in its first two weeks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718054721/https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2018-07-23/p/4/|title=\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u9031\u9593 \u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2018\u5e7407\u670809\u65e5\uff5e2018\u5e7407\u670815\u65e5 31\uff5e40\u4f4d {{!}} ORICON NEWS|date=2018-07-18|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref> The title track charted at number 20 on ''Billboard's'' [[World Digital Songs]] chart and number 88 on the international Gaon Digital Chart.\n\n== Track listing ==\n'''Digital download'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.melon.com/album/detail.htm?albumId=10181640|title=#Cookie Jar|website=www.melon.com|language=ko|access-date=2018-07-21}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing =\n| title1 = #Cookie Jar\n| length1 = 3:33\n| lyrics1 = MEG.ME\n| music1 = {{hlist|Efraim Faramir Sixten Fransesco Vindalf Cederqvist Leo|Mats Koray Genc|Gavin Jones|Saima Iren Mian|[[Dsign Music|Ronny Vidar Svendsen]]|[[Dsign Music|Anne Judith Wik]]|[[Dsign Music|Nermin Harambasic]]}}\n| title2 = Aitai-tai (lit. \"Miss You, I Always\")\n| length2 = 3:14\n| lyrics2 = {{hlist|H.Toyosaki|MonoTree}}\n| music2 = MonoTree\n| title3 = 'Cause It's You\n| length3 = 2:59\n| lyrics3 = Agehasprings\n| music3 = {{hlist|[[Dsign Music|Anne Judith Wik]]|[[Dsign Music|Ronny Vidar Svendsen]]|[[Dsign Music|Nermin Harambasic]]|[[Dsign Music|Jin Suk Choi]]|Justin Stein|Park Geun-tae}}\n| title4 = Dumb Dumb\n| note4 = Japanese version\n| length4 = 3:22\n| lyrics4 = {{hlist|Seo Ji-eum|Kim Dong-hyun|Hidenori Tanaka}}\n| music4 = {{hlist|LDN Noise|Taylor Parks|Deanna Dellacioppa}}\n| title5 = Russian Roulette\n| note5 = Japanese version\n| length5 = 3:31\n| lyrics5 = {{hlist|Jo Yun-gyeong|Hajime Watanabe}}\n| music5 = {{hlist|Albi Albertsson|Belle Humble|Markus Lindell}}\n| title6 = Red Flavor\n| note6 = Japanese version\n| length6 = 3:11\n| lyrics6 = {{hlist|Kenzie|Kami Kaoru}}\n| music6 = {{hlist|Daniel Caesar|Ludwig Lindell}}\n| total_length = 19:49\n}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!Chart (2018)\n!Peak\nposition\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Japanese Albums ([[Oricon Albums Chart|Oricon]])<ref name=\":0\" />\n|3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Japan Hot Albums ([[Billboard Japan|''Billboard'']])<ref name=\":1\" />\n|4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |US World Albums (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\":2\" />\n|13\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Red Velvet}